Analysis end date

Source: R/dates.R
aendt.Rd

Derives analysis end date based on (incomplete) dates given as character

Usage

aendt(.self, dtc)

Arguments

.self

data.frame Input data set

dtc

character Name of date variable

Value

.self with added analysis end date variables

Mighty

Type

derivation

Depends

  • .self.{dtc}

Outputs

  • AENDT

  • AENDTF

Examples

x <- pharmaversesdtm::ae |>
  dplyr::select(USUBJID, AEENDTC) |>
  aendt("AEENDTC")

print(x)
#> # A tibble: 1,191 × 4
#>    USUBJID     AEENDTC    AENDT      AENDTF

#>  5 01-701-1023 2012-08-30 2012-08-30 NA    
#>  6 01-701-1023 NA         NA         NA    
#>  7 01-701-1023 2012-08-30 2012-08-30 NA    
#>  8 01-701-1028 NA         NA         NA    
#>  9 01-701-1028 NA         NA         NA

#> # ℹ 1,181 more rows

x |>
  dplyr::filter(!is.na(AENDTF)) |>
  print()
